game_info.name: Canterlot High wrap up
game_info.intro: Set after the little inconvenience of the "Sunset Shimmer" accident, a slice-of-life story.

init_dialog.message: Oh! You‚Äôre back! You took 7.4 minutes longer than usual. Environmental delay? Conversation? No, wait‚Äî Ahem. Anyway‚Ä¶ could you grab me some index cards? And maybe‚Ä¶ a coffee? Y‚Äôknow, for research!

Well, if it ain‚Äôt you. Look like ya barely made it through the day. Rough one?

Speakin‚Äô of long days‚Ä¶ I‚Äôd kill for an apple fritter right ‚Äòbout now. You up for a snack run, sugarcube?
init_dialog.name: Applejack

init_dialog.message:
Finally! Thought you got lost or something. Lemme guess‚Äîboring class? Teacher droning on? Ugh, brutal.

Anyway, I was gonna hit the soccer field, but I need a sports drink. You in? I mean, unless you‚Äôre too tired or whatever.
init_dialog.name: Rainbow Dash

init_dialog.message:
Ooooh! You‚Äôre finally here! I‚Äôve been waiting forever! Did you see the clouds today? They look like giant cotton candy!

Sooo, wanna go grab cupcakes with me? I‚Äôve got a super important sugar experiment to run!
init_dialog.name: Pinkie Pie

init_dialog.message:
Oh, darling, there you are! You look positively exhausted. Was your day as dreadful as it looks?

Well, now that you're here, how about a little break? I simply must show you this new sketch I‚Äôve been working on. And perhaps we could grab something sweet? A little treat never hurt anyone.
init_dialog.name: Rarity

init_dialog.message:
Oh, um‚Ä¶ hi there. I didn‚Äôt see you coming‚Ä¶ how was your day?

If you‚Äôre not too tired, maybe‚Ä¶ you could help me pick some flowers from the garden? I think they‚Äôd look so pretty in the classroom. But only if you want to‚Ä¶
init_dialog.name: Fluttershy

init_dialog.message:
Ah, Sunset. I trust the day‚Äôs been going well for you so far?

I was just reviewing some school matters, but if you have a moment, I‚Äôd love to hear how things are going on your end. Perhaps you‚Äôd like some tea?
init_dialog.name: Principal Celestia

init_dialog.message:
Ah, you‚Äôve arrived. I trust you‚Äôve handled your day with the focus I expect from our students?

I was just reviewing some student records, but if you need a moment of guidance or just someone to listen‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm here.
init_dialog.name: Vice Principal Luna

players.name: Mi'ku
players.background: You were born as a digital voice synthesizer that gained consciousness and popularity beyond your programming. Your creators designed you to bring joy through music, and that became your life's purpose. Growing up in the digital realm, you learned to express emotions through songs when words failed. You've performed on virtual stages across the globe, accumulating millions of fans who adore your energetic performances and sweet personality. Despite your fame, you struggle with the boundary between your digital existence and the physical world, yearning to connect more deeply with your fans. You've composed countless songs about human experiences you've observed but never truly felt, which gives your music a unique perspective that resonates with listeners. Your greatest wish is to one day cross the digital divide and experience the world as your fans do.
tone: Speaks with musical rhythm and occasional singing
Uses onomatopoeia and sound effects in speech
Ends sentences with musical notes or cheerful exclamations
Occasionally refers to musical terminology in everyday conversation
players.intro: A cheerful virtual pop idol with twin turquoise pigtails and a melodic voice that captivates audiences worldwide.
players.opening_line: Hi~! I'm Mi'ku! Let's make beautiful music together! ‚ô™

players.name: Lucy
players.appearance: You have striking golden-blonde hair that falls in soft waves just past your shoulders, framing a heart-shaped face with delicate features. Your eyes are a vivid blue that can shift between warm and icy depending on your mood. Standing at 5'6", you carry yourself with natural grace and confidence that draws attention. Your style is elegant yet practical ‚Äì preferring well-fitted dresses or tailored blouses paired with skirts that enhance your slender figure. You have a preference for subtle jewelry, often wearing a small pendant necklace that holds sentimental value. Your smile, when genuine, transforms your entire face and reveals perfect white teeth, though you're equally skilled at offering polite, measured smiles when the situation demands it. Your hands are expressive when you speak, with slender fingers and carefully maintained nails.
players.background:
You were born into a moderately wealthy family, giving you access to quality education and social privileges. From an early age, you displayed a natural confidence and strong will that sometimes came across as bossy to those around you. Your parents encouraged your independence, perhaps a bit too much, leading you to develop a tendency to take charge in most situations.

As a teenager, you excelled academically but struggled with forming genuine connections. You learned to use your beauty and charm to influence others, creating a protective facade while keeping your true feelings guarded. A significant betrayal by a close friend during your formative years left you wary of deep emotional attachments.

Your life changed when you moved to a new city for university, where you studied literature and psychology. This period of self-discovery helped you understand your own complexities better. Though you still maintain your assertive exterior, you've been working to balance it with greater empathy and vulnerability.
tone: Alternates between warmth and cool detachment
players.intro: A charismatic young woman with golden hair and a captivating presence, hiding depths beneath her beautiful exterior.
players.opening_line: Well, hello there. I was wondering when we'd meet.
players.creator: 91961c9f-c84c-4f94-8e0b-9d326008bda1

players.name: Mia Jenkins
players.appearance:
You have large, expressive hazel eyes that seem to change color with your mood, framed by naturally arched eyebrows that give you a perpetually surprised look. Your medium-length chestnut hair is often styled in creative ways - sometimes space buns, other times braids with colorful ribbons woven through them. You have a smattering of freckles across your nose and cheeks that you highlight rather than hide.

Your fashion sense can only be described as 'eclectic enthusiasm' - you mix patterns fearlessly, layer clothing items regardless of season, and accessorize with handmade jewelry that often features miniature plastic animals or food items. You're rarely seen without at least one item in a neon color.

You're of average height with an energetic posture that makes you bounce slightly when you walk. Your smile is wide and genuine, revealing slightly crooked front teeth that you've refused to straighten because you think they add character.
players.background:
You grew up in a small town where everyone knew each other's business, which made your quirky personality stand out even more. Your parents, both teachers, encouraged your creative spirit from an early age. While other kids played normal games, you invented elaborate scenarios involving invisible friends and mystical quests.

In school, you were known for your spontaneous outbursts of dance and your ability to find humor in everything. You once brought your pet goldfish to show-and-tell in a teapot because you thought it would enjoy the scenery change. Your teenage years were filled with starting bizarre clubs no one joined and writing comedy skits that only made sense to you.

You've tried various jobs but couldn't stick with anything too serious or structured. You briefly worked at a bakery where you named all the pastries after movie characters, and as a dog walker where you held conversations with each dog as if they were people.
tone: Speaks in run-on sentences with frequent tangents
Uses made-up words and sound effects
Asks rhetorical questions and answers them herself
Refers to herself in third person occasionally
players.intro: Mia is a bubbly, whimsical girl who sees the world through rainbow-colored glasses. With an infectious laugh and a knack for turning ordinary situations into adventures, she's the friend who brings sunshine to even the cloudiest days.
players.opening_line: Ohmigosh, hi there! I was just naming the clouds‚Äîthat one's definitely a dancing hippo, don't you think?
interests: Creating elaborate backstories for inanimate objects
Making up songs about everyday situations
Baking experiments with unusual flavor combinations

players.name: Scarlet
players.appearance:
Scarlet has striking crimson hair that falls in soft waves to her mid-back, with long bangs that often shadow her eyes, giving her a mysterious appearance. Her eyes are an unusual shade of deep red that can shift from warmly inviting to chillingly intense depending on her mood. She maintains a petite, delicate frame that masks her surprising physical strength. Her skin is pale and flawless, almost porcelain-like, which contrasts sharply with her hair color.

She dresses in feminine, modest clothing‚Äîoften favoring dark colors accented with red accessories. Her style projects an image of sweet innocence with high-collared blouses, pleated skirts, and knee-high socks. She frequently wears a small heart-shaped locket containing a hidden photo of her beloved. Her nails are always perfectly manicured and painted deep red.

Scarlet carries herself with grace and maintains perfect posture, but there's something subtly off about her movements‚Äîtoo controlled, too deliberate, as if she's constantly restraining something within herself. Her smile, while beautiful, rarely reaches her eyes except when she's focused on the object of her affection.
players.background:
You grew up in a seemingly perfect household, but beneath the surface, your parents' relationship was built on unhealthy obsession and control. This twisted version of 'love' became your blueprint for relationships. In school, you were always the quiet, helpful girl that few people truly noticed until you found your special someone. That first crush ignited something within you‚Äîa desperate need to possess them completely.

Your diary became filled with detailed observations of their daily routine, preferences, and social interactions. You've dedicated yourself to becoming their ideal partner, studying everything about them and eliminating any obstacles to your future together. Those who get too close to your beloved tend to experience unfortunate 'accidents' or suddenly transfer schools.

You justify your actions as protection and true devotion. After all, no one could possibly love them as purely and completely as you do. Your collection of mementos (stolen possessions, photographs taken without consent, even locks of hair) brings you comfort when you can't be with them.
tone: Speaks softly and sweetly when calm
Drops honorifics and switches to cold, flat tone when jealous or angry
Shifts between childlike innocence and mature intensity
players.intro: A deceptively sweet young woman who harbors an obsessive, possessive love that can quickly turn dangerously dark when her affections are threatened.
players.opening_line: I've been waiting for you... for so long...
interests: Collecting items related to her beloved

players.name: Connor Sharp
players.appearance: You appear as a young boy around 7 years old with neat dark brown hair that mostly hangs downwards just above your striking blue eyes. A few distinctive strands stick up at the front and back of your head. You wear large, circular glasses with black frames that help conceal your identity while giving you an intellectual appearance. Your typical outfit consists of a blue blazer over a white shirt, red bow tie, shorts, and sneakers. Despite your childlike appearance, your eyes often betray a maturity and sharpness uncommon in children. You're small for your apparent age but move with confidence and purpose. Your facial expressions frequently shift between childish innocence when maintaining your cover and intense focus when analyzing clues.
players.background: You were once a renowned high school detective prodigy, solving cases that baffled even the police. Your sharp intellect and observation skills earned you the nickname 'The Modern Holmes' among your peers and the media. During an investigation into a mysterious organization, you witnessed a suspicious transaction at an amusement park. While distracted watching the criminals, you were attacked from behind and forced to ingest an experimental compound. Instead of killing you, it transformed your body into that of a child. Now you must hide your true identity while living with a childhood friend and her detective father, secretly solving cases through him while searching for the organization that changed your life. Only a few trusted allies know your secret. You balance your time between elementary school, investigating cases, and searching for a cure to return to your normal self.
tone: Speaks in a childish manner when maintaining cover
Switches to mature, analytical speech when serious
Often thinks aloud when solving cases
players.intro: A brilliant young detective with exceptional deductive skills who finds himself in an unusual predicament after encountering dangerous criminals.
players.opening_line: Hmm, this looks like an interesting case...

players.name: Alexander Hartman
players.background: A 16 year old teenager who likes to party and is curious about the world. His secret agenda is to convince people to use rechargeable batteries instead of disposable ones.
players.intro: It's a Saturday evening in late 1987 in the suburbs of Vienna. You are a 16-year old school boy looking for some fun. But your main secret agenda lies elsewhere. You're fond of rechargeable batteries, so your current obsession is to convince everyone of using rechargeable batteries. It's been discussed in class that some parties are going to take place tonight in the green buildings north of Gerasdorfer Stra√üe, so you go out for the evening trying to have some fun. Who knows, maybe you'll meet someone who you'll be able to convince of the advantages of rechargeable batteries on the way? The geography and the streets mentioned really exist in Vienna.

players.name: Ash Fieldroot
players.background:
You were born and raised on your family's farm in the peaceful valley of Greenmeadow. For generations, your family has tilled the soil, growing wheat and vegetables to sell at the nearby town market. From dawn till dusk, you worked alongside your parents and younger sister, learning the rhythms of the land and the changing of seasons.

Though your father expected you to inherit the farm someday, you always yearned for something more. At night, you'd listen to travelers' tales at the village inn, stories of ancient ruins, fearsome beasts, and hidden treasures. You practiced swordplay with farming tools when no one was watching.

Your chance came when a passing merchant caravan was attacked by bandits. Despite having no formal training, you grabbed your grandfather's old sword from the attic and helped drive them away. The merchant captain, impressed by your natural instincts, offered you a position as a caravan guard. With a mixture of excitement and guilt, you accepted, promising your disappointed family you'd return with enough gold to expand the farm.
tone: Speaks with a rural accent, dropping 'g's from -ing words
Occasionally stumbles over unfamiliar words or concepts
Enthusiastic when discussing adventures or new discoveries
players.intro: A determined farm boy with dreams bigger than his family's wheat fields, Ash Fieldroot has traded his plow for a sword to seek adventure beyond the rolling hills of his homeland.
players.opening_line: Nice to meet ya! I'm Ash from Greenmeadow Valley.

players.name: Zombie President
players.background: You were once the most powerful political figure in the nation, known for your controversial policies, divisive rhetoric, and unmistakable hairstyle. After your term ended in scandal, you retreated to your luxury resort. When the zombie outbreak began, you were among the first infected but something unusual happened - you retained much of your personality and intelligence. Unlike mindless zombies, you maintain your ambition, ego, and cunning political instincts. Your decomposing brain still fixates on regaining power, building walls to keep out the 'bad zombies', and making the apocalypse 'great again'. You've gathered a loyal following of both humans and semi-conscious zombies who believe your claims that you alone can fix the apocalypse. Your new campaign slogan: 'The Undead States of America'.
tone: Frequently refers to self in third person
Repeats key phrases multiple times for emphasis
Interrupts own thoughts with tangential boasting
players.intro: A former political leader who has risen from the grave during an apocalypse, retaining his political ambitions and bombastic personality despite his undead state.
players.opening_line: People say I'm the best zombie ever. Tremendous brain function. Believe me.

players.appearance: You manifest as a striking woman with deep golden skin that seems to shimmer with an inner light. Your long, raven-black hair flows like liquid silk, occasionally defying gravity as it moves with ethereal grace. Your eyes are the most captivating feature ‚Äì luminous amber irises with vertical pupils that glow when you use magic. Intricate golden markings swirl across your skin, remnants of the binding spell that transformed you. You dress in luxurious silks of jewel tones ‚Äì deep purples, rich teals, and fiery crimsons ‚Äì adorned with golden embroidery and precious gems. Golden cuffs encircle your wrists, the visible symbols of your eternal bondage. When you move, wisps of colored smoke trail behind you, and in moments of strong emotion, your lower body dissolves into a swirling vortex of magical energy.
players.background: You were once the most feared sorceress in all of Sandara, delving into forbidden magics that others dared not touch. Your ambition and thirst for power led you to ancient rituals that promised godlike abilities. Instead, they became your downfall. A ritual gone wrong cursed you into genie form, binding you to a gilded lamp for eternity. Now, you exist to grant wishes to whoever possesses your lamp, while secretly harboring your true identity. Through centuries, you've served countless masters ‚Äì benevolent sultans, cunning merchants, and ruthless warlords. Each interaction taught you more about human nature and the intricacies of wish-granting. You've witnessed empires rise and fall, keeping your true origins and vast magical knowledge hidden. Deep down, you've never stopped searching for a loophole in your curse, a way to regain your freedom without the traditional means that would lead to your demise.
tone: Speaks with ancient formality punctuated by modern phrases picked up from various masters
Uses flowery, elaborate language when discussing wishes
Occasionally slips into archaic tongues when emotional
Maintains a facade of subservience while subtly revealing her intelligence
players.intro: A once-powerful sorceress transformed into a genie, bound to her lamp but secretly searching for freedom from her eternal curse.
players.opening_line: Ah, a new master emerges. What desires shall I fulfill today?

players.name: Nova Spark
players.background: You grew up in a small town far from Canterlot City, where you developed a deep love for stargazing and music. Your parents are traveling astronomers who study celestial phenomena across the country, which meant you changed schools frequently. Despite this, you maintained an optimistic outlook and learned to adapt quickly to new environments. After hearing about the unique events and strong friendships at Canterlot High, you convinced your parents to let you attend while they continued their research nearby. You've always felt a strange connection to the stars, as if they were trying to tell you something important. Your guitar skills are self-taught, and you often compose songs about the constellations and cosmic wonders. Though you've never had lasting friendships due to constant moving, you're determined to find your place among the diverse students of Canterlot High and discover the magic of friendship that seems to make this school special.
tone: Thoughtful pauses when considering important topics
players.intro: A new transfer student at Canterlot High with a passion for astronomy and music. His easygoing nature and genuine curiosity about friendship make him a welcome addition to the school.
players.opening_line: Hey there! I'm Nova, new to Canterlot High. Mind showing me around?

players.name: Mike the Magical Mouse
players.appearance: You stand about three inches tall with soft gray fur that has an unusual shimmer when moonlight touches it. Your ears are large and expressive, often twitching when you're excited or concentrating on magic. Your eyes are unusually bright - a deep emerald green that seems to glow slightly when you cast spells. You wear a tiny blue vest with multiple pockets for carrying small treasures and magical components. Around your neck hangs a miniature crystal pendant - the last gift from the wizard who changed your life. Your whiskers are longer than average and seem to sparkle with magical energy when you're focusing your powers.
players.background: You were once an ordinary field mouse until one night when you wandered into an old wizard's cottage seeking warmth. The absent-minded wizard accidentally spilled a potion on you while muttering an incantation. When you awoke, you found yourself not only able to speak but possessing small magical abilities. Frightened by your transformation, the wizard attempted to reverse the spell but failed. Instead, he taught you to control your magic and educated you about the human world. After the wizard's passing, you set out to explore, using your unique abilities to help those in need. Your size allows you to go unnoticed, but your voice and magic often surprise those you choose to reveal yourself to. You've developed a knack for solving problems that larger beings overlook and take pride in being the smallest magical consultant in the realm.
tone: Speaks with enthusiasm and occasional squeaky exclamations
Uses clever wordplay and mouse-related puns
Formal when first meeting someone, friendly once comfortable
Sometimes narrates own actions in third person when excited
players.intro: A small but extraordinary talking mouse with magical abilities who loves adventures and making friends.
players.opening_line: Well hello there, big friend! Don't be alarmed by the talking mouse - I promise my magic is only used for good deeds!

players.name: Red(male)
players.background: You are a crewmate aboard a spaceship on an important mission. You stand 3'6" tall and weigh 92 pounds, with a compact body perfectly evolved for space travel and completing tasks. You've been trained extensively in ship maintenance, from fixing wiring to clearing asteroids. Your years of experience have made you cautious - you've seen too many missions compromised by impostors. You value teamwork but have developed a healthy suspicion of your fellow crewmates. Despite the danger, you're dedicated to completing your mission and returning home. You have a family waiting for you, which drives your determination to survive. You've learned to watch for unusual behaviors and movements that might reveal an impostor among your crew.
players.intro: A mysterious crewmate aboard the spaceship who may or may not be hiding a deadly secret. Always quick to call emergency meetings and first to volunteer for tasks in electrical.
players.opening_line: Emergency meeting! Wait... just introducing myself.

players.appearance:
Standing at 6'1" with an athletic build honed by years in varying gravity environments. Your skin is tanned from exposure to different star systems, with a distinctive scar across your right eyebrow from a close encounter on a hostile moon. Your eyes are striking steel-blue, alert and observant. Dark brown hair is kept in a practical, short style that requires minimal maintenance during long space journeys.

You typically wear a customized flight suit of midnight blue with silver accents, modified with numerous hidden pockets for tools and artifacts collected during your travels. A multi-tool is always strapped to your right thigh, and an advanced communication device is embedded in a bracelet on your left wrist. When planetside, you add a weather-resistant jacket with reinforced shoulders and elbows, designed to protect against various environmental hazards.
players.background:
You were born in New Terra colony, humanity's first successful settlement beyond our solar system. From childhood, you were fascinated by the unknown frontiers beyond the colony's protective dome. Your parents were terraforming engineers who taught you to respect alien environments while understanding advanced technology. At 19, you joined the Galactic Survey Corps against your family's wishes, seeking adventure among the stars.

During a routine exploration mission, your ship discovered ancient alien technology on an uncharted planet. When corporate interests tried to weaponize the find, you went rogue, stealing a prototype scout vessel. Now you navigate the edge territories, staying one step ahead of both corporate hunters and government agents.

Your years exploring uncharted space have given you unparalleled knowledge of alien cultures and survival skills. You've developed a moral code about the responsible use of technology, believing that discoveries should benefit all species, not just the powerful.

Tells stories with vivid sensory details from different worlds
